Battle Hall Pokémon

The following Pokémon are used in the Battle Hall. Every species that can be legally entered into any Battle Frontier facility has one moveset, with the exception of Wormadam, which has one for each cloak. Pokémon are divided into four groups:

  1. Group 1: Pokémon with a base stat total of 340 or lower
  2. Group 2: Pokémon with a base stat total between 340 and 439
  3. Group 3: Pokémon with a base stat total between 440 and 499
  4. Group 4: Pokémon with a base stat total of 500 or above

The list of Pokémon used in the other battle facilities is different from the list used here. Please see the Battle Frontier Pokémon page for information.

  • Group 1
  • Group 2
  • Group 3
  • Group 4

Opposing Pokémon Mechanics

In the Battle Hall, the player is required to select a type, and will fight a Pokémon belonging to that type. Pokémon with two types can be battled in either of their types.

For the first 170 battles, the player begins each type at Rank 1. For every victory over a type, the rank will increase, to a maximum of 10. Once the player has won 170 battles, the enemy Pokémon are always from Rank 10. The group, IVs, and level of the opposing Pokémon depend on what rank the player has selected.

Group Ranks
Group 1 1-5
Group 2 3-8
Group 3 6-10
Group 4 9-10

IVs start at 8 for Rank 1 and increase by 2 every rank, for a total of 26 at Rank 10.

The formula that describes how enemy Pokémon's levels scale is shown here. At level 100, no opposing Pokémon will ever be higher than level 96. The exception to this is Multi Battles, where enemy Pokémon match the highest level of the players' Pokémon.

Frontier Brain Argenta will always use a Pokémon from the same group as the player's for her Silver Print battle, and a Pokémon from Group 4 for her Gold Print battle. Her Pokémon is chosen randomly, so it may not match the type that the player has chosen for the battle. In both of her battles, her Pokémon will have 31 IVs and match the level of the player's Pokémon.

Some additional resources:

  • This page contains a damage calculator with all the movesets of Battle Frontier Pokémon pre-loaded, using the numbers for each set. Sets where the number begins with the letter 'H' are used by the Battle Hall. Remember that you will need to update the IVs yourself in accordance with the Trainer faced.
  • This post contains some Speed values associated with enemy Pokémon with 26 IVs and at level 96. This can be useful for determining what kinds of Speed benchmarks your Pokémon will need to hit to accomplish their goals.
  • This spreadsheet contains many general resources about the Platinum/HeartGold/SoulSilver battle facilities in one place; you may find the spreadsheet easier to use than this webpage. This website has some corrections that, as of this writing, aren't present in the spreadsheet, such as: Miltank is listed with number 539 twice; Pokémon with neutral natures may have the incorrect nature listed; the list of Trainers is missing some data for the first 100 Trainers in the list.
